# Day 09 - Package Management (apt)

## Theory
- On a Linux server you install all software through a package manager
- Never go to websites and downloading — use apt
- apt is the package manager for Ubuntu/Linux/Debian
- This is how you set up servers

## Commands Learned

### apt — Package Manager
| Command | What it does |
|---------|-------------|
| `sudo apt update` | Refresh the list of available packages from internet |
| `sudo apt upgrade` | Upgrade all installed packages to latest version |
| `sudo apt install package` | Install a package |
| `sudo apt install -y package` | Install without asking yes/no (for scripts) |
| `sudo apt remove package` | Remove a package |
| `sudo apt purge package` | Remove package AND its config files |
| `sudo apt autoremove` | Remove packages no longer needed |
| `apt search keyword` | Search for packages matching keyword |
| `apt show package` | Show details about a package |
| `dpkg -l` | List all installed packages |
| `dpkg -l | grep nginx` | Check if nginx is installed |
| `dpkg -l | wc -l` | Count installed packages |
| `which program` | Check if program is installed and find it |
| `program --version` | Check version of installed program |

